    <title>How to install VIM plugins</title>
    <link>https://kienngd.github.io/blog/how_to_install_vim_plugins/</link>
    <pubDate>Wed, 14 Oct 2020 09:08:18 &#43;0700</pubDate><author>
        <name>Kien Nguyen</name>
    </author><guid>https://kienngd.github.io/blog/how_to_install_vim_plugins/</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<p>Hello, today we will to learn 2 of many ways to install and use VIM plugins. I use Ubuntu 20.04 to test. Have fun!</p>
<p>If you want to install plugin named <strong>nerdtree</strong>,</p>
<p>1st way: Copy plugin files to: <strong>~/.vim/pack/vendor/start</strong> and they will be load when you launch VIM</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">cp -r nerdtree ~/.vim/pack/vendor/start/
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p>Then inside VIM, you can use command: <strong>:NERDTree</strong></p>]]></description>
